$LNG['questions'][1][1]['title']	= 'Step 1';
$LNG['questions'][1][1]['body']		= <<<BODY
<p>This part of the Tutorial describes the main buildings of the game. It advises about what to build at the beginning, and what you will need to build a successful Empire.</p>
<h3>Solar Plant:</h3>
<p>The Solar Plant generates energy, which is used to power the production of the three main resources. For this production to actually happen, the energy used in (mine) production should ideally not exceed the energy generated. When the mix of production uses more energy than is available, the usage turns negative, and this will result in a production drop for all mines. Avoid this as much as possible..</p>
<h3>Metal mine:</h3>
<p>Metal is one of the three main resources available in the game. It is used for almost anything you can build or research. Therefore early expansion of the metal mine is advisable.</p>
<h3>Crystal mine and Deuterium synthesizer</h3>
<p>Crystal is also used for buildings, ships, and research. It is produced at a lesser rate than metal, which makes it a more valuable and highly prized resource.
   Deuterium is a source of energy, used in very specific buildings and researches, and primarily as fuel for ships. It is difficult to obtain, thereby consuming more energy per level than other mines.</p>
BODY;
$LNG['questions'][1][2]['title']	= 'Step 2';
$LNG['questions'][1][2]['body']		= <<<BODY
<p>To protect and expand your Empire you need defence and shipbuilding capacities. Performing the necessary research followed by the construction of a Hangar, you then may begin the construction of your Planetary Defense and Fleet. The details can be found here:</p>
<h3>The Hangar:</h3>
<p>The hangar produces all the defences and ships that are available in the game. More advanced ships will have higher technological requirements in order to be built. An overview of the technological requirements for all defences and ships can be found under the title 'Technology' in the menu. Hovering over greyed out 'unavailable' ships or defences will also provide an indication of missing buildings or research. While leveling up the Shipyard is a prerequisite for the building of more advanced defences and ships, increasing the Shipyard level also serves to construct your ships and defences at a faster pace.</p>
<h3>The Research Lab:</h3>
<p>These are used to research technologies which enable the construction of more advanced buildings, ships and defenses. Research can also increase the speed of ships, or give bonuses in armor, weaponry and shielding. Increasing the Research Lab level also enables research to proceed at a faster pace.</p>
<h3>Robot Factory:</h3>
<p>The Robot Factory is an important component that leads to the building of a hangar, and increasing its level will lead to significant reduction in building construction times.</p>
BODY;
