$LNG['questions'][1][3]['body']		= <<<BODY
<p>This part of the tutorial is dedicated to the defence of your planet and the first actions of your fleet.</p>
<h3>Galaxy View:</h3>
<p>Galaxy View is frequently used to find the locations of planets of other players. You will find detailed information on planets including your own, and you can send your fleet on missions directly from the same page. In addition you can contact other players by Private Message, or if you possess Spy Probes, you can spy their planets and moons.</p>
<h3>Sending Fleets:</h3>
<p>You can send your fleet directly from the Galaxy View or by going to "Fleets" tab. The first step is to select the quantities of the types of ships you wish to send on a mission. After confirming, the second step is to enter the target coordinates (that you obtained from the Galaxy View), select 'Planet', 'Debris' (for recycling) or 'Moon', and select the speed at which your fleet will be flying (default is full speed; 100%). After confirming again, the final step is selecting an action you wish to perform with your fleet, such as "Attack", "Colonize", "Transfer", "Transport" or "Deploy" etc.</p>
<h3>Defence:</h3>
<p>Protecting your own planet and resources requires at minimum some defence in addition to your fleet. Defences offer some protection against an enemy fleet at the moment of attack. In contrast to fleets which once destroyed are permanently so; 70% of destroyed defences get repaired.</p>
BODY;
